  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180ºC/ 160ºC (fan)/ 350ºF/ Gas 4</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Wash the<strong> leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in 550ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once melted, add the<strong> sliced leek</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> leek</strong> has softened, add the<strong> chicken stock</strong> and <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong></p>\n<p>Massage the <strong>oil </strong>into the <strong>kale </strong>until it's evenly coated</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until turning golden and crisp </p>\n<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the<strong> cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> smoked streaky bacon </strong>and cook for 5 min, turning once halfway until golden and crisp</p>\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>bacon</strong> to kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>potatoes</strong> are fork-tender, add the <strong>cannellini beans</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> and cook for 2 min further, stirring until everything is warmed through</p>\n<p>Squeeze in the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy leek, potato &amp; bean stew </strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1484.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>bacon</strong> roughly </p>\n<p>Serve the <strong>creamy leek, potato &amp; bean stew</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy kale</strong> and <strong>bacon</strong></p>\n<p>Garnish with a wedge of<strong> lemon</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 8,
